The second form is normal mathematical notation but has lots of necessary b=
rackets, making it harder to read and also must easier to miss a bracket.<b=
r>
In the  final form note that the <span class=3D"m">+</span> is written <i>b=
elow the fraction-line</i> to show that the rest of the expression is also =
meant to be there too.<br>
On this page and others at this site, we will use the much more convenient =
<b>list notation</b> <span class=3D"m">[ a; b, c, d, ... ]</span>.
