<h3 id=3D"section6.1">6.1                     A Simple Way to find =E2=88=
=9An
</h3>
Here is another way to introduce or "discover" continued fractions based on=
 finding the square-root of a
number. This method differs from those earlier at the top of the page in th=
at it gives us
an <i>infinitely long</i> continued fraction, but this turns out to have so=
me very useful properties.
<p>
Take, for example, =E2=88=9A5.  The nearest square below 5 is 4, so we know=
 =E2=88=9A5 begins with 2.  Let's write:<br>
</p><div class=3D"indent m">
=E2=88=9A5 =3D 2 + x <br>
5 =3D (2 + x)<sup>2</sup><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp; =3D 4 + 4x + x<sup>2</sup><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp; =3D 4 + x( 4 + x)
</div>
If we rearrange the last line we have
<div class=3D"indent m">
5 =E2=88=92 4 =3D x(4 + x)<br>
1 =3D x(4 + x)<br>
<table class=3D"m fracTBL"><tbody><tr><td rowspan=3D"2"> x =3D </td><td cla=
ss=3D"top">1</td></tr>
<tr><td>4 + x</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
Now we have a formula for x, we can use it on the right-hand side and get:
<div class=3D"indent m">
<table class=3D"fracTBL" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"1" style=3D"empty=
-cells:show;border-collapse:separate">
<tbody><tr><td rowspan=3D"2"><span style=3D"border:2px solid red"> x</span>=
</td>
    <td class=3D"vtop red big" rowspan=3D"2"> &nbsp;=E2=86=92&nbsp; </td>
   <td class=3D"top" style=3D"border-top:2px solid red;border-left:2px soli=
d red;border-right:2px solid red">1</td>
   <td class=3D"vtop big" style=3D"color:limegreen" rowspan=3D"2">  &nbsp;=
=E2=86=92&nbsp; </td>
   <td class=3D"top" colspan=3D"2">1</td><td class=3D"vtop big" style=3D"co=
lor:dodgerblue" rowspan=3D"2">  &nbsp;=E2=86=92&nbsp; ...</td></tr>
<tr><td class=3D"vtop" style=3D"border-bottom:2px solid red;border-left:2px=
 solid red;border-right:2px solid red">4 + <span style=3D"border:2px dotted=
 limegreen">x</span></td>
    <td class=3D"vtop">4 + </td>
   <td rowspan=3D"2">
	   <table class=3D"fracTBL" style=3D"border:2px dotted limegreen"><tbody><=
tr><td class=3D"top">1</td></tr>
