/tr></tbody></table>
   </td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=3D"5">&nbsp;</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
When we repeat this, we get a <b>continued fraction</b> <i>which never ends=
!</i><br>
If we put x back in the original line: <span class=3D"m">=E2=88=9A5 =3D 2 +=
 x</span>
<div class=3D"indent">
<table class=3D"fracTBL m">
<tbody><tr><td rowspan=3D"2" class=3D"vmid"> =E2=88=9A5&nbsp;=3D&nbsp;2 + <=
/td>
