td></td><td rowspan=3D"2">4 + </td><td class=3D"top" colspan=3D"4"> 1 </td>=
</tr><tr><td colspan=3D"3"></td><td rowspan=3D"2">2 + </td><td class=3D"top=
" colspan=3D"3"> 1 </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3D"3"></td><td>4 + ...</td></t=
r></tbody></table></span>
</div>
This is our first example of a general continued fraction since the numerat=
ors of the fractions are
not 1.  It happens that each of the above simplify to give a simple CF.  Ca=
