  This method is completely general and applies to all square roots.





 <a id=3D"sqrts"> </a>
</p><h3 id=3D"section6.3">6.3
            All square-root continued fractions eventually repeat

 </h3>

All square-root simple CFs end with a periodic pattern that repeats forever=
.

<h4 id=3D"section6.3.1">6.3.1 Notation for Periodic CFs
</h4>

Using the method above method, we can produce=20
 the following table of some square root continued fractions.  What pattern=
s can you spot in the table? =20
To find out more, look at the books in the References section at the bottom=
 of this page.

<pre>=E2=88=9A2 =3D <span class=3D"m">[ 1; 2, 2, 2, 2, 2, 2, 2, 2, ... ]</s=
pan> =3D <span class=3D"m">1</span> then repeat <span class=3D"m">2</span>
=E2=88=9A3 =3D <span class=3D"m">[ 1; 1, 2, 1, 2, 1, 2, 1, 2, ... ]</span> =
=3D <span class=3D"m">1</span> then repeat <span class=3D"m">1,2</span>
=E2=88=9A4 =3D <span class=3D"m">2</span>
=E2=88=9A5 =3D <span class=3D"m">[ 2; 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, ... ]</span> =
=3D <span class=3D"m">2</span> then repeat <span class=3D"m">4</span>
=E2=88=9A6 =3D <span class=3D"m">[ 2; 2, 4, 2, 4, 2, 4, 2, 4, ... ]</span> =
=3D <span class=3D"m">2</span> then repeat <span class=3D"m">2,4</span>
=E2=88=9A7 =3D <span class=3D"m">[ 2; 1, 1, 1, 4, 1, 1, 1, 4, ... ]</span> =
=3D <span class=3D"m">2</span> then repeat <span class=3D"m">1,1,1,4</span>
=E2=88=9A8 =3D <span class=3D"m">[ 2; 1, 4, 1, 4, 1, 4, 1, 4, ... ]</span> =
=3D <span class=3D"m">2</span> then repeat <span class=3D"m">1,4</span>
=E2=88=9A9 =3D <span class=3D"m">3</span>
=E2=88=9A10=3D <span class=3D"m">[ 3; 6, 6, 6, 6, 6, 6, 6, 6, ... ]</span> =
=3D <span class=3D"m">3</span> then repeat <span class=3D"m">6</span>
=E2=88=9A11=3D <span class=3D"m">[ 3; 3, 6, 3, 6, 3, 6, 3, 6, ... ]</span> =
=3D <span class=3D"m">3</span> then repeat <span class=3D"m">3,6</span>
=E2=88=9A12=3D <span class=3D"m">[ 3; 2, 6, 2, 6, 2, 6, 2, 6, ... ]</span> =
=3D <span class=3D"m">3</span> then repeat <span class=3D"m">2,6</span>
