We clearly need a notation for the periodic part of a CF.

<div class=3D"indent">
Notation:  we will put a line over the repeating part, in the same way that=
 repeating decimals are often written, for example:<br>
<div class=3D"indent" style=3D"padding-top: 4px">
  =E2=88=9A 2 =3D <span class=3D"m">[ 1; 2, 2, 2, 2, ... ]</span> =3D <span=
 class=3D"m">[ 1; <span class=3D"overline">2</span> ]</span>
</div>
<div class=3D"indent" style=3D"padding-top: 4px">  <span class=3D"m">[a; b,=
 &nbsp;c, d, &nbsp;c, d, .... ] =3D [ a; b, <span class=3D"overline">c, d</=
span> ] </span>
</div>
The repeating part is always the final part of a CF since it indicates numb=
ers that repeat in a cycle for ever.
</div>

