pan> is ambiguous - it can mean either of two values.<br>
As always in mathematics, we therefore make an arbitrary choice=20
- a <b>convention</b> - that the continued fraction <span class=3D"m">a;b,c=
,d,...</span> <b>always=20
represents a positive value</b> and we
<b>prefix a continued fraction with a minus sign to represent a negative va=
lue</b>.  <br>
With this convention we can still represent the other value:=20
