d></tr>
<tr><th>Numerator</th><td class=3D"top dim">1</td><td class=3D"top">a</td><=
td class=3D"top">b=C3=97a+1</td>
   <td class=3D"top">c=C3=97( ba+1 )+a</td><td class=3D"top">d=C3=97(c(ba+1=
)+a) + (ba+1)</td><td rowspan=3D"2">...</td></tr>
<tr><th>Denom</th><td class=3D"dim">0</td><td>1</td><td>b=C3=971+0</td><td>=
c=C3=97b+1</td><td>d=C3=97(cb+1) + b</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>

There is an example in the next section:

<a id=3D"fibphi"></a>
<h3 id=3D"section9.2">9.2            The Convergents of Phi's CF are Ratios=
 of Fibonacci Numbers!
</h3>

When we try this for the golden section number Phi =3D <span class=3D"m"> [=
1;<span class=3D"overline"> 1 </span> ] </span> we get....
<div class=3D"center">
<table cellspacing=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"5" class=3D"paleBorder centerPage c=
enter m">
