Pickett and Coleman have a simple CF for <span class=3D"mathsym">=CF=80</sp=
an> - the numerators are all 1 - but which has fractions as the terms in th=
e denominators
and these fractions are the Harmonic Series (which increases without limit =
so the resulting simple CF will converge):
<div class=3D"center">
<table class=3D"fracTBL1 m">
<tbody><tr><td class=3D"top mathsym">=CF=80</td><td rowspan=3D"2"> =3D [1; =
1, 1/2, 1/3, 1/4, 1/5, ... ]</td></tr>
<tr><td>2</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
However, it converges very slowly. Stopping at 1000 terms we have 3.14124..=
.=20
with only the first 3 dps being accurate.


